President Muhammadu Buhari has vowed to use every resource available at his disposal to deal decisively in order to address the various security challenges bedeviling the nation. The President gave the assurance at the end of the National Security Council meeting, at the Presidential Villa, Abuja.  Addressing State House Correspondents at the end of the meeting, National Security Adviser (NSA), Maj. Gen. Babagana Monguno (rtd), said the Council received a comprehensive brief by the Secretary to the Government of the Federation and Chairman of presidential Taskforce in COVID-19,Â  on the gains made so far, highlighting areas of concern that need urgent attention and possible solutions.  Our correspondent, Raliat Adenekan reports that Monguno also briefed the Security Council on issues that revolve around the insurgency in the north east, armed banditry, as well as kidnappings which has been on the increase in recent times, calling for collective efforts to tackle the challenges.